SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE UNF OFFICE OF GOVERNMENTAL RELATIONS DEVELOPS AND IMPLEMENTS STRATEGIES AND PROGRAMS TO ATTAIN PUBLIC FUNDING GOALS, AND TO FOSTER MUTUALLY SUPPORTIVE, ON-GOING RELATIONSHIPS WITH ELECTED OFFICIALS, EXECUTIVE BRANCH LEADERS, OTHER EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTIONS, AS WELL AS UNF'S PUBLIC AND PRIVATE CONSTITUENTS. THE OFFICE REPORTS TO THE UNF COMMUNITY IMPORTANT LEGISLATIVE, GOVERNANCE, AND POLICY ISSUES THAT THAT SPECIFICALLY IMPACT UNF OR PUBLIC HIGHER EDUCATION.

THE ORGANIZATION HOLDS ASSETS ON BEHALF OF A RELATED ORGANIZATION, THE MUSEUM OF CONTEMPORARY ARTS JACKSONVILLE, INC. (THE MUSEUM; EIN: 59-0689705). THE MUSEUM TRANSFERRED INVESTMENT FUNDS TO THE ORGANIZATION THAT ARE BEING HELD AS A TERM ENDOWMENT ON BEHALF OF THE MUSEUM. IN ACCORDANCE WITH GASB 84, THESE ASSETS ARE NOT REFLECTED ON THE ORGANIZATION'S FINANCIAL STATEMENTS, RATHER, THEY ARE REPORTED WITHIN THE STATEMENT OF FIDUCIARY NET POSITION. AS A RESULT, THEY HAVE NOT BEEN INCLUDED ON FORM 990, BUT ARE BEING REPORTED IN THIS SUPPLEMENTARY DISCLOSURE.
THE USES FOR THE UNF FOUNDATION ENDOWMENT FUNDS ARE FOR SCHOLARSHIPS, FELLOWSHIPS, STUDY ABROAD, PROFESSORSHIPS, EDUCATIONAL PROGRAMS, RESEARCH, AND TECHNOLOGY ENHANCEMENT.

THE FOUNDATION IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE; ACCORDINGLY, THE ACCOMPANYING FINANCIAL STATEMENTS DO NOT REFLECT A PROVISION OR LIABILITY FOR FEDERAL AND STATE INCOME TAXES. THE FOUNDATION HAS DETERMINED THAT IT DOES NOT HAVE ANY MATERIAL UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS AS OF JUNE 30, 2023 AND 2022.

GrantsOtherAsstToIndivInUSGrp.GrantTypeTxt: SCHOLARSHIPS, FIRST GENERATION SCHOLARSHIPS, FELLOWSHIPS, AND STUDY ABROAD

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE UNIVERSITY OF NORTH FLORIDA FOUNDATION SCHOLARSHIPS, FELLOWSHIPS AND STUDY ABROAD ARE AWARDED BASED ON THE SPECIFIC CRITERIA FOR EACH AWARD PER DONOR AGREEMENT (E.G., GPA, NUMBER OF REQUIRED CLASSSROOM HOURS, STUDENT CLASSIFICATION, MAJOR, ETC.). THE ACCOUNT FUND MANAGER ADVERTISES THE SCHOLARSHIP AND RECEIVES THE STUDENT'S INFORMATION BASED ON THE CRITERIA. FOUNDATION ACCOUNTING REVIEWS THE SCHOLARSHIP AWARD AND SUPPORTING DOCUMENTATION TO ENSURE COMPLIANCE PRIOR TO FORWARDING TO THE UNIVERSITY ENROLLMENT SERVICES DEPARTMENT FOR PROCESSING. ENROLLMENT SERVICES THEN REVIEWS TO ENSURE THE STUDENT IS NOT BEING AWARDED ABOVE THE COST OF EDUCATION, AFTER WHICH, THE STUDENT RECEIVES THE FUNDS AND FOUNDATION ACCOUNTING REIMBURSES THE UNIVERSITY FOR THE SCHOLARSHIP AWARD. OTHER OUTSTANDING AWARDS ARE PROVIDED TO GRADUATING SENIORS AT THE SPRING CONVOCATION. OUTSTANDING ALUMNI AWARD IS PROVIDED BY ALUMNI SERVICES AT EACH GRADUATION BASED ON THE GRADUATE SELECTED BY THE COMMITTEE.

THE ORGANIZATION RELIED ON THE UNIVERSITY OF NORTH FLORIDA, A RELATED ORGANIZATION, TO ESTABLISH THE COMPENSATION OF THE ORGANIZATION'S TOP MANAGEMENT OFFICIAL. THE UNIVERSITY OF NORTH FLORIDA USED THE FOLLOWING METHODS TO ESTABLISH COMPENSATION: WRITTEN EMPLOYMENT CONTRACT, COMPENSATION SURVEY OR STUDY AND APPROVAL BY THE BOARD OR COMPENSATION COMMITTEE.

DAVID SZYMANSKI, THE FORMER UNF PRESIDENT, AND FORMER OFFICER FOR UNF FOUNDATION, RECEIVES AN ANNUAL BONUS PAYMENTS FOR PERFORMANCE AND RETENTION. THE PERFORMANCE IS DETERMINED AFTER YEAR-END AND PAID BY THE ORGANIZATION.
THE ORGANIZATION IS REPORTING THE NUMBER OF ITEMS CONTRIBUTED.

THE NUMBER OF EMPLOYEES REPORTED ON PART V, LINE 2A REPRESENTS THE NUMBER OF EMPLOYEES OF THE FILING ORGANIZATION DURING THE TAX YEAR 2022 WHICH WERE REPORTED ON FORM W-3 BY UNF, A CONTROLLING RELATED ENTITY. SIMILARLY, THE SALARY EXPENSES REFLECTED ON FORM 990, PART IX WERE ALL REPORTED ON THE FORM 941, EMPLOYER'S QUARTERLY FEDERAL TAX RETURN, OF UNF AND REIMBURSED BY UNF FOUNDATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 1A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE FOUNDATION BOARD SHALL CONSIST OF THE FOLLOWING MEMBERS: 1.) CHAIR OF THE FOUNDATION 2.) PRESIDENT OF UNIVERSITY 3.) IMMEDIATE PAST CHAIR OF THE FOUNDATION 4.) CHAIR-ELECT OF THE FOUNDATION 5.) CHAIR, DEVELOPMENT COMMITTEE 6.) CHAIR, GOVERNANCE COMMITTEE 7.) CHAIR, FINANCE AND AUDIT COMMITTEE 8.) CHAIR, INVESTMENT COMMITTEE 9.) CHAIR, GRANTS COMMITTEE 10.) BOARD OF TRUSTEE DESIGNEE 11.) UNF FINANCING CORPORATE DESIGNEE 12.) MOCA DESIGNEE 13.) AT-LARGE MEMBERS FROM THE FOUNDATION AT THE DISCRETION OF THE FOUNDATION CHAIR AND THE UNIVERSITY PRESIDENT 14.) EX-OFFICIO, THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR/SECRETARY OF THE FOUNDATION 15.) EX-OFFICIO, THE TREASURER OF THE FOUNDATION THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE SHALL MEET AT THE CALL OF THE CHAIR OF THE FOUNDATION. ONE-THIRD OF THE MEMBERS SHALL REPRESENT A QUORUM OF THE COMMITTEE. THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE SHALL HAVE AND MAY EXERCISE ALL POWERS AND AUTHORITY OF THE FOUNDATION BOARD BETWEEN MEETINGS OF THE FOUNDATION BOARD AND SHALL BE EMPOWERED TO ACT ON BEHALF OF THE FOUNDATION BOARD IN CASES WHERE A MEETING OF THE FULL FOUNDATION BOARD WILL NOT OCCUR WITHIN THE TIME FRAME NECESSARY FOR APPROVING AN ACTION DEEMED TO BE IN THE BEST INTEREST OF THE FOUNDATION. ACTIONS BY THE EXEUCTIVE COMMITTEE SHALL BE SUBJECT ONLY TO SUCH RESTRICTIONS AS THE FOUNDATION BOARD MAY FROM TIME TO TIME SPECIFY. A REPORT OF THE ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE SHALL BE PRESENTED TO THE FOUNDATION BOARD IN A TIMELY MANNER.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 WAS PREPARED BY A PAID PREPARER. THE FINAL DRAFT WAS REVIEWED BY THE FOUNDATION'S BOARD OF DIRECTORS WITH THE FOUNDATION'S STAFF. AFTER BOARD APPROVAL, THE RETURN WAS FILED WITH THE IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: BOARD MEMBERS ANNUALLY COMPLETE THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST FORMS. THE UNF FOUNDATION MANAGEMENT REVIEWS THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST FORMS FOR ANY NOTED CONFLICT OF INTEREST. IF ANY EXIST AND REQUIRES A BOARD VOTE, THE BOARD OF DIRECTOR MEMBER RECUSES HIMSELF OR HERSELF FROM VOTING ON THE ISSUE. IT IS NOTED IN THE OFFICIAL MINUTES THAT THE BOARD MEMBER ACKNOWLEDGED THE CONFLICT AND RECUSED FROM VOTING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FOUNDATION EMPLOYEES ARE EMPLOYED BY THE UNIVERSITY OF NORTH FLORIDA. THE FOUNDATION REIMBURSES THE UNIVERSITY FOR PAYROLL COSTS (SALARIES AND FRINGE BENEFITS) FOR THE FOUNDATION'S PORTION OF THE PAYROLL COSTS. THE CALCULATION OF THIS REIMBURSEMENT IS BASED ON THE PERCENTAGE OF EACH EMPLOYEE'S SALARY AND BENEFITS THAT IS RELATED TO THEIR SERVICES PERFORMED FOR THE FOUNDATION. THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND ALUMNI ENGAGEMENT'S COMPENSATION (TOP MANAGEMENT OFFICIAL) IS REVIEWED AND SET BY THE PRESIDENT OF THE UNIVERSITY OF NORTH FLORIDA OR DESIGNEE, IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE UNIVERSITY POLICIES. THESE POLICIES REQUIRE THAT COMPARABLE DATA BE USED TO DETERMINE THAT MANAGEMENT IS COMPENSATED FAIRLY AND COMPETITIVELY WHEN COMPENSATED TO SIMILAR ROLES IN OTHER UNIVERSITIES NATIONALLY.
